---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Back-in-Stock Alerts in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for back-in-stock alerts by inventory events, consent, urgency, pricing context, sources, and implementation tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Interest-based inventory alerts and segments','Flexible event logic and behavioral profiles','Requires dependable inventory events','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail restock alerts across email and SMS','Accessible automation and channel workflows','SMS eligibility and inventory timing need care','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean stores with simple waitlist sequences','Focused alert and follow-up workflows','Validate real-time stock integration','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Restock messaging beside transactional email','Broad messaging capabilities','More manual inventory-event design','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Simple campaign announcements','Native product selection','Not a dedicated real-time alert engine','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Back-in-stock email has unusually clear intent, but only if the inventory event is accurate. The best app sends once to a person who asked, stops after purchase, and does not create false urgency when stock is limited again.</p><p>We prioritize explicit alert consent, inventory freshness, duplicate suppression, and measurable conversion. Confirm current vendor pricing and the stock-alert integration’s behavior before launch.</p><h2>Shortlist</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First workflow</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Product-interest alert':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Restock email/SMS':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Waitlist sequence':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Availability update':'Product announcement'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for back-in-stock alerts</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the store can represent the requested product, consent, stock event, and purchase state separately. An alert subscriber should not be treated as a general promotional audience without a clear permission basis.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Test one product and one stock event first, then measure alert-to-order conversion, duplicate sends, complaints, and unsubscribes. High intent makes the workflow measurable, not automatically profitable for every catalog.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports an inventory-event test; can use Shopify signals.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; real-time integrations and SMS affect total cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plan limits and any separate alert-app costs.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Behavioral product alerts</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event segmentation.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple waitlist workflow</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused sequence operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Native announcement only</td><td>Shopify Email</td><td>Fast basic campaign setup.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/use-cases/back-in-stock">back-in-stock guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
